# AGENTS.local.md

Jarvis project convention.

Codex does not auto-load `AGENTS.local.md`. Keep private notes here if you want a local, gitignored scratchpad for:

- machine-specific commands
- personal verification preferences
- temporary do-not-run reminders
- local tool paths

If you want Codex to apply some of these instructions automatically, copy the safe subset into:

- `~/.codex/AGENTS.override.md` for a personal global override, or
- `AGENTS.override.md` in the working directory when you intentionally want a repo-local override

Suggested structure:

```md
# Local notes

- Prefer local smoke checks before Kubernetes checks.
- My preferred module test command:
  `mvn -pl apps/<module> -am test`
- Local-only tools:
  `/path/to/private/tool`
```
